The Delta State Police Command said it has arrested a suspected armed robber, Udensi David at Udumuje-Ugboko community in Ndokwa North East Local Government Area of the state. The Police also recovered a double barrel gun with live cartridge from the suspect. The Delta State Acting Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Edafe Bright disclosed this in a statement signed and made available to DAILY POST. The Police Image maker said the suspect was arrested after a distressed call from an indigene of Udumudje-Ugboko to the Divisional Police Officer
Issele-Uku Division on the 8/3/2021 at about 2100hrs that he suspected a man to be in possession of firearm. According to him, “Immediately patrol team was deployed to the scene, one Udensi David ‘m’ of Udumudje-Ugboko was arrested.” He noted that the case is under investigation.